---
// Load your data with fetch(), Astro.fetchContent(), etc.
const response = await fetch(`https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon?limit=150`);
const result = await response.json();
const allPokemon = result.results;
const firstPage = allPokemon.slice(0, 10);
---

<strong>Pokemons:</strong>

<br>

{firstPage.map(p => {
    return <a href="/pokemon/${p.name}">View {p.name}</a><br>;
})}

<br>

<p>If the number of items in the4 first page is less than the page size then we don't need to display the link to the next page.</p>
<a href="/pokemon/page/2">Go to next page</a>

